{{Han etym}}
Ancient simplification of {{och-l|䨮}}, which is in turn {{Han compound|雨|彗|c1=s|c2=p|t1=rain|ls=psc|nocap=1}}.

===Etymology===
{{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} considers this to be related to {{cog|qfa-tak|-}} words: {{cog|tai-pro||*hnəiᴬ¹|snow}}, {{cog|qfa-kms-pro|*ʔnuːi¹||snow}}.

{{zh-ref|Starostin}} reconstructs {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*suăt||snow}}, comparing this with {{cog|bo|སད||frost, cold air, cold, coldness}}, but this connection may be unlikely considering the phonetic part of this character.

